 
   Project: Microbe PHP Framework
     About: Lightweight PHP framework for simple site construction
   Version: 0.1.1 (developement)
     Begin: 2017 may 01
   Current: 2019 march 16
    Author: Microbe PHP Framework author <microbe-framework@protonmail.com>
 Copyright: Microbe PHP Framework author <microbe-framework@protonmail.com>
   License: MIT license
    Source: https://github.com/microbe-framework/microbe/

One of goals of this project is Router-View architecture.
The application render a layout directly after routing.
You must define routing rules and create corresponding views.
Controllers unnecessary at all.
This approach applicable for simple sites and landing pages.

Project under developement.
Please report about bugs.

1. Short help.

1.1. Unzip or git clone package in root directory of your website.
1.2. Correct '.htaccess' and 'index.php'.
1.3. Edit routes in '/config/routes.json'.
1.4. Add data models in '/application/model/' if needs.
1.5. Add views' render routines in '/application/views/' if needs.
1.6. Edit action handlers in '/application/controllers/' if needs.
1.7. Edit loader for Your own classes in '/application/AppLoader.inc.php'.
1.8. Place Your layouts, templates, blocks in corresponding 'views' directory.
1.9. Enjoy.

2. Default directories structure:

/www-root/
    /README
    /README.md
    /LICENSE
    /.htaccess
    /index.php
    /config/
        /config.txt
        /routes.json
    /application/
        /AppLoader.inc.php
        /routers
            /AppRouter.class.php
            ...
        /models
            /AppModel.class.php
            ...
        /views
            /AppView.class.php
            ...
        /controllers
            /AppController.class.php
            ...
         ...
    /framework/
        /library/
            ...
        /classes/
            ...
    /views/
        /layouts/
            ...
        /templates/
            ...
        /blocks/
            ...
    /vendor/
        ...
    /assets/
        /css/
            /microbe.css
        /js/
            /microbe.js
        /images/
            /icons/
                ...
            ....

3. Changes.

Version 0.1.1
Date 2019 march 16
    Enclose framework classes into namespace 'Microbe'
    Add database connection support (MySqli only).
    Add classes for recordsets & connections.
    Add Model class.
    Old loader '/application/load.inc.php' replaced with Loader and AppLoader classes.
    Add HttpRequest class.
    Detects and handle site prefix if site locates not in server root.
    Change directories structure.
    Add assets directory and place js, css and images into assets.
    Extends set of configuration variables for config.txt.

Version 0.1.0
Date 2018 february 23
    First release.
